The chatSessions options picker briefly flashes "Open Picker" when no options should be displayed. The `chatSessionHasOptions` context key was set to `true` before evaluating option group `when` expressions, causing the `ChatSessionPrimaryPickerAction` to appear momentarily before being hidden.

## Changes

**File: `src/vs/workbench/contrib/chat/browser/widget/input/chatInputPart.ts`**

In `refreshChatSessionPickers()`:
- Moved `chatSessionHasOptions.set(true)` to after computing visible option groups
- Added early return with `hideAll()` when `visibleGroupIds.size === 0`

The context key now accurately reflects whether visible options exist after `when` expression evaluation, preventing the menu item from appearing when no options are available.

```typescript
// Compute which option groups should be visible based on when expressions
const visibleGroupIds = new Set<string>();
for (const optionGroup of optionGroups) {
    if (!this.chatSessionsService.getSessionOption(ctx.chatSessionResource, optionGroup.id)) {
        continue;
    }
    if (this.evaluateOptionGroupVisibility(optionGroup)) {
        visibleGroupIds.add(optionGroup.id);
    }
}

// Only show the picker if there are visible option groups
if (visibleGroupIds.size === 0) {
    return hideAll();
}

this.chatSessionHasOptions.set(true);
```

